comment.content:
I just had a backpack, so it was straight to security for me. There was a larger queue than the last time, but I was still through in six minutes. No doubt due in large part to no longer requiring to take things from bags.
I was leaving from Gate 21, which is around the corner. I had WiFi connection previously, but when I got to the gate I had none. I don't know if it was a wider issue or just an issue with the gates furthest away from the main body of the departure lounge.
